ationship to him (the soul is female; also in 3-74 I perceived myself as female, but did not know why; yet it was a valid perception). Within this system, the Lord (Shiva, Krishna, Christ) fills the universe + indeed this is how I experienced Valis (this is also said of the Buddha in has diamond body). Thus all this (the festive preparations for the return of the bridegroom - which fits in with the collapse or telescoping of time), my sense of being female, + Valis - i.e. the Lord - filling the universe + found in e.g., the debris + trash of the alley. There is another confirmation: my experience with God that day kaymone was down here + we smoked hash, when I was aware of God the Father + his intense love for me: love as his very nature - the presence of love was a palpable thing, as real as the physical laws of creation. This love shows up in \"Tears but, see, this explains why I saw Acts as now; for the sense that Christ had just now left + would very soon be returning, time had to collapse - into, really, another kind of time entirely where 2000 years became - + was experienced as - a very short interval. This is, a course, eschatological time, but it is also the time (or time-sense) that makes possible the mode or state - both ontological + existential - of joyous eager anticipation of what is imminently pected + this renders real the passionate bride, bridegroom relationship between worshiper + Christ which is the essential mystical expersence found also in islam, + in pan-Indian thought, at this point you are not dealing with any single given religion - as Kabir shows. There + is another point + a crucial one. that shows up in my letter to rust about v E-27 This is something I am sure of. in 2-3-74 I was perceiving myself - the two-mirrors phenomenon - which is to say, thinking about oe own thinking. Christ is in me (this accords with the Cartesian representation-of world theory/realization); viz: when I saw Christ (i.e. Valis) in + as world, this was really 