ich physical law + moral law are combined justification is an adjustment in the cosmic order; thus in terms of the order as it - the adjust it was before the justification Here ment - is a perturbation [in that order]. the where my template idea comes in: is cosmic order is justified -aligned - to a template differing slightly from it (as If the template is ideal in God's mind: what the order should be; it is intelligible + having been thought by God it now is as the physical order itself; the physical cosmos conforms to it) -2 have it. What we call \"justification I s a sharp, radical change of your status An improved status) in the cosmic order that cannot be explained mechanisti cally + could not occur in the Greco E-92 Babylonian closed system that existed (2) bits Gnosticism + against which Hans Jonas contrasts the Gnostic \"Faustian or oven cosmos. This change of status does not occur due to prior (i.e. efficient) causes (prior states in the system regarded as a closed system - + thus in terms of Spinoza's view of the universe could not occur; but his view is the closed-system view that is in contrast to the Gnostic system, then I assume that Judaism, like the Greco-Babylonian system is mechanistic + closed, + it is precisely against this that Paul revolts. Hence in Paul's doctrine of justification, something entirely new has come into the world-order or at least into the understanding (apper‐ t 3-74 they, did not ception of the world-order. proceed from antecedent causes - exactly as sensed at the time. This is impossible even in stoicism - in all systems prior to the Pauline. Does this imply a trans‐ mundane power, as Gnosticism teaches - that is, reaching into the world-order (cosmos) from outside? + not an internal adjustment? will guess yes. This is precisely my I insight: that no internal adjustment within closed system can account for it; it a is analogous to an organism assimilating negative entropy from its environment it implies an outside. Thus in the messenger E-93 vision the machinery of retribution equals the closed-system cosmos of the Judo-Greco-Babylonians the Gnostic Faustian transmundane concept would seem to be the case; Spinoza's deterministic system in which all changes are the result of prior states is reactionary - a throwback to the mechanistic cosmology of pre Gnostic antiquity now, a decided link to Gnosticism is established if my meta-abstraction is equated with the Gnosis, i.e. a cog‐ nitive act. This does not answer all questions but it answers the specific question that his been bothering me: the Greco-Babylonian closed cosmos vs what Hans Jonas calls the Faustian or Gnostic: in favor of the latter. The key word that occurred to me as I drove home is: ewth. Orthodox Xtian or Gnostic, this is the common element of the two: + it means P18tos is the Messianic age. 2-3-74 is this may not verify Gnosticism but it verifies the o - soteriological being whom we know as Christ. The Messenger vision implies (by reason of the term \"Messenger\") Gnosticism (\"angel\" is not meant, t think). Thus the insight (moksa) I had on the freeway tonight identifies Valis as Christ i just had a terrifying insight: the man shut up in Darkness in \"Tears\" who emits the \"single dreadful shrick\" is the crucified Christ - Jason Taverner (who is also Dionysos/Zagreus.) yet also the E-94 white-bearded old king on horse. back is Christ as eschatological judge! He presides over his own sacrifice. This is the old Christ of revelation + Daniel sacrificing himself",
